                                <p>“The unleashed power of the atom has changed everything save our modes of thinking, and we thus drift toward unparalleled catastrophe.” - Albert Einstein</p>
                                <p>
                                    Dear Delegates,
                                </p>
                                <p>As the Chairperson of the International Atomic and Energy Agency (IAEA) it gives me immense pleasure in welcoming you to DSMUN 2016. I am currently studying in Grade 12 at The Doon School with an avid interest in Dramatics, Squash And Model UN. I have pursued MUN at school since Grade 9, starting off as an official in the Security Council to participating in the capacities of a delegate and Deputy Chairperson. I have gone on to represent my school at all sessions of the much-revered Harvard MUN.</p>
                                <p>As far as the committee goes, the IAEA serves a great purpose of restricting nuclear war and saving the world from the scourge of war. The mandate of the IAEA at this year’s conference is not restricted to a monitoring body; but will focus on limiting the nuclear arsenal of nations. Moreover, the committee will be instrumental in formulating policies regarding safeguards of the IAEA and discussing the nuclear regime in North Korea led by the military dictator Kim Jong-un. Delegates must take note that the IAEA has been entrusted with key roles under the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT), which has been crucial in influencing decisions made by the committee in the past.</p>
                                <p>The agenda for the committee is as follows:</p>
                                <p><ul><li><b>Nuclear free zones</b></li>
                                <li><b>North Korea Hydrogen Bomb test</b></li></ul></p>
                                <p>I expect several things from the delegates over the course of the conference: firstly, a high level of debate and an ability to form blocs and an understanding one’s critical role as stakeholders of world powers. Lobbying is crucial to any MUN experience and delegates much utilize this strategy to be a step ahead at DSMUN.</p>
                                <p>I look forward to meeting you at Chandbagh.</p>
